title: Docs on the Fox with the St. Charles Dems - Finding the Money
description:
The St. Charles Township Democrats invite you to the first installment of our new documentary screening series, where we explore critical issues affecting us locally, nationally, and globally.

For our inaugural screening, we’ll be watching “Finding the Money”, a thought-provoking documentary that challenges common misconceptions about the national debt and deficit spending.

With growing concerns from both sides of the aisle about deficit spending and how to fund key programs at the national level, this film offers a timely and insightful look at the myths surrounding the national debt.

We are gauging interest in attendance for this event. We have been in contact with the film’s producers and may have the opportunity to host a post-screening Q&A or discussion on the real-world application of these ideas in politics with individuals involved in the film.

Please RSVP to help us assess interest, communicate with the film’s producers, and secure the necessary screening kit and resources.

Join us for an evening of engaging discussion, learning, and community conversation. All are welcome!

description:
Please sign up to attend a free screening of the groundbreaking documentary “Bad Faith: Christian Nationalism's Unholy War on Democracy.”

This powerful and disturbing documentary reveals how Christian Nationalism has become one of the most powerful political forces in the nation by spreading fear and anger and distorting political issues into battles between good and evil. Their ultimate goal – highlighted in their Project 2025 manifesto – is the destruction of church-state separation, inclusive religious freedom, LGBTQ+ and women’s rights, inclusive public schools and more… all while enshrining their narrow, religious beliefs into law for us to suffer under.

Financed by the secretive Council for National Policy, the movement has succeeded in infiltrating American politics and has become one of the most powerful political forces in the nation. Discover the origins of this organized grasp for power, and learn about the grassroots coalition of secular and interfaith leaders who are bravely confronting the grave threat Christian Nationalism poses to our democracy.

title: Join DeKalb Dems at Juneteenth in Stonecrest
description:
The City of Stonecrest is celebrating Juneteenth bigger than ever before this year by hosting it's 3rd annual Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom on Saturday June 14, 2025.

DeKalb Dems will have a visibility tent and we need volunteers to assist with set up and act as Ambassadors who listen to citizen's concerns, offer ways we can support them, and talk about what they can do to safeguard our freedom.

Juneteenth commemorates the effective end of slavery in the United States. Two years after President Lincoln signed the Emancipation Proclamation, news reached Texas and, upon learning they were free, former slaves immediately began celebrating with prayer, feasting, song, and dance. The Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom will celebrate African American culture, heritage, and, most importantly, abolishment of slavery.

The Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom will feature an expanded kidz zone, live performances, food trucks, vendors, and fireworks show. It is a place for all races, nationalities, and religions to join hands and truthfully acknowledge a period in history that shaped and continues to influence our society today, according to a news release. This event is free and open to the public, and we encourage everyone to attend and learn more about the history and culture of Juneteenth!

Please sign up for a shift below and be a part of this Celebration of Freedom.

description:
The Collin County Democratic Party, in partnership with 50501, invites you to join us as we Stand Up for Democracy! This is a critical moment to raise our voices against the forces threatening our democracy, social security, constitutional rights, and the very foundations of our nation. While this event is sponsored by the Collin County Democratic Party, it is nonpartisan in nature, as we believe ALL Americans must be unified in this fight for our rights.

This Event WILL go on rain or shine!

### We’re taking a stand against:

- Donald Trump and his MAGA extremists, who continue to undermine free elections and push authoritarian agendas.

- Elon Musk, whose unchecked influence and platforming of far-right extremism endanger our democracy.

- The so-called Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE), a shadowy effort to dismantle vital government functions.

- All their enablers—corporate greed, voter suppression, attacks on marginalized communities, and the erosion of our civil liberties.

### Why Protest Now? 
Our democracy is under siege. Social Security is at risk. The Constitution is being twisted to serve the powerful. Donald Trump "doesn't know" if everyone deserves due process (hint: it's what we're DUE!). Whether it’s attacks on reproductive rights, climate inaction, or the relentless assault on truth and justice—we’ve had enough!

Join us to demand accountability, defend our freedoms, and fight for a future where democracy works for ALL of us—not just the wealthy and well-connected.

📢 Bring your signs, your anger, and your determination! Together, we will peacefully but assertively make our voices heard.

#StandUpForDemocracy #SaveOurFuture #DefendTheConstitution

📍 Location: Southeast corner of Preston Road and Gaylord Parkway in Frisco, TX. Feel free to park behind the Jared's Jewelers at 3110 Preston Rd, Frisco, TX 75034; we will congregate on the sidewalk on the SE corner of Preston and Gaylord.

title: So You Want to Run for Office – Pride Month Edition: Advance Equality, Run For Office
description:
Everyone should have the right to run – and come to the voter as they are. This Pride Month, join us to explore what it means to run for office if you are an LGBTQ+ leader in the making. 

  

Being out and running for office can feel especially challenging right now. But it’s also why this training can be especially important. Acceptance, representation, a voice at the table, and the protection of our rights all work in tandem. Representation is how we got to a Supreme Court decision about marriage equality. More representation, especially at the grassroots level, is how we will get to have and keep more equality – in all ways – the law of the land. 

  

Are you a member of the LGBTQ+ community and would you like to run for office? Are you perhaps considering a run for elected office but haven’t yet made the commitment to run or filed your candidacy? Then this virtual live training is for you! 

  

Join our expert trainer and come away with insights and next steps on the following topics:

*   Understanding the steps necessary to run for office
    
*   Best practices for choosing which office to run for
    
*   Discerning if running is the right decision for you – especially if you are LGBTQ+ and have never run for office but are thinking about it
    
*   Identifying what kinds of supports you’ll need to run for office
    
*   Preparing for sharing your decision to run with your support network

description:

NO KINGS is a national day of action and mass mobilization in response to the increasing authoritarian excesses and corruption of the Trump administration.
